<p>I had a look at this <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4525482/in-sinatraruby-how-should-i-create-global-variables-which-are-assigned-values">question</a>, but this is only for variables. I would like to create an object of a class and use it globally in Sinatra</p>  <p>I am doing something like the following and works fine:</p>  <pre><code>require 'sinatra' require 'MyClass'  set :port, 8080 set :static, true  get '/' do   erb :myform, :locals =&gt; {'value' =&gt; "Give a value."} end  post '/hello/' do   param_1 = params[:param_1]   param_2 = params[:param_2]    @obj = MyClass.new   value = @obj.run(param_1, param_2)    erb :myform, :locals =&gt; {'value' =&gt; value} end </code></pre>  <p>But I would like to create the object outside the post. Maybe something like:</p>  <pre><code>require 'sinatra' require 'MyClass'  set :port, 8080 set :static, true  @obj = MyClass.new  get '/' do   erb :myform, :locals =&gt; {'value' =&gt; "Give a value."} end  post '/hello/' do   param_1 = params[:param_1]   param_2 = params[:param_2]    value = @obj.run(param_1, param_2)    erb :myform, :locals =&gt; {'value' =&gt; value} end </code></pre>  <p>However, the latter does not work as I get null in the value. </p>  <p>How can I create the object once and then use it globally?</p>